WEBVTT

00:02.252 --> 00:04.243
NARRATOR:
A few weeks ago, an invisible dome

00:04.421 --> 00:06.412
crashed down on Chester's Mill,

00:06.590 --> 00:08.501
cutting us off
from the rest of the world.

00:08.675 --> 00:11.007
Why the dome is here
or What mysteries lie ahead,

00:11.178 --> 00:14.591
we still don 't know.
Every day it tests our limits,

00:14.765 --> 00:17.347
bringing out the best
and the worst in us.

00:18.769 --> 00:21.226
Some say we '/I be stuck here
forever,

00:22.022 --> 00:25.765
but we will never stop ﬁghting
to ﬁnd a way out.

00:26.527 --> 00:28.267
REBECCA:
Big Jim threw the egg off the Cliff.

00:28.445 --> 00:29.776
That proves it's the power source.

00:29.947 --> 00:31.983
- The dome's contracting.
- You mean it's shrinking?

00:32.157 --> 00:33.693
REBECCA:
At its present rate

00:33.867 --> 00:35.983
- it won't be long before the dome--
- Crushes us?

00:36.161 --> 00:37.697
- This is your fault.
- Where's Melanie?

00:37.871 --> 00:40.078
I painted a vision.
It may show us how to save her.

00:40.249 --> 00:42.114
[SCREAMING]

00:42.292 --> 00:43.623
Grab my hand.

00:43.794 --> 00:45.500
In my dream,
I saw Melanie disappear,

00:45.671 --> 00:48.128
- but I didn't know it meant that.
- I love you.

00:51.260 --> 00:52.670
You know why?

00:52.844 --> 00:54.550
Because she's supposed
to be with me, Jim.

00:55.681 --> 00:57.387
[GRUNTING]

01:03.188 --> 01:04.303
We have to go after Melanie.

01:04.481 --> 01:06.392
It's too dangerous.
No one's going anywhere.

01:07.025 --> 01:08.435
- Can you see anything?
BARBIE: No.

01:08.610 --> 01:09.645
[RUMBUNG]

01:09.820 --> 01:11.560
Oh, my God.
There's another earthquake.

01:16.577 --> 01:18.158
SAM:
Where do you think the crater leads?

01:18.328 --> 01:19.943
Maybe it's another tunnel,
like at school.

01:20.122 --> 01:21.157
It could lead to Zenith.

01:21.331 --> 01:23.447
Or somewhere else.
Anywhere but here would be great.

01:26.003 --> 01:29.541
We gotta check it out,
but we gotta do it right.

01:29.715 --> 01:31.831
Not risking anyone else's life.

01:32.009 --> 01:33.749
Help me! Help!

01:33.927 --> 01:35.758
Pauline. Pauline.

01:35.929 --> 01:38.011
Lay her down on her side.
Hunter, I need your shirt.

01:38.181 --> 01:40.137
- What happened?
- Lyle. Lyle stabbed her.

01:40.309 --> 01:41.765
- Where is he now?
- He's dead.

01:43.186 --> 01:44.847
HUNTER:
Here.

01:45.022 --> 01:47.559
- I tried to stop the bleeding.
- Our supplies are at the school.

01:47.733 --> 01:50.395
- Well, let's get there now.
- Prius is at the edge of the woods.

01:50.569 --> 01:52.434
PAULINE: Julia.
- I'm right here.

01:52.613 --> 01:55.946
After I was stabbed, I had a vision.

01:56.116 --> 01:57.401
The dome chose you.

01:58.452 --> 02:01.194
But you're not alone.

02:01.371 --> 02:03.953
There's someone else,
but I can't see his face.

02:04.124 --> 02:06.991
He-- He doesn't know he's the one.

02:12.299 --> 02:14.255
BARBIE: Come on, get the stretcher
underneath her.

02:14.426 --> 02:16.087
I gotta keep pressure on this wound.

02:16.261 --> 02:17.876
- Rebecca, you're coming with us.
- Okay.

02:18.055 --> 02:19.716
SAM:
Make some room. Here we go.

02:19.890 --> 02:21.346
JIM: Yeah, I got it.
SAM: Ready?

02:21.516 --> 02:24.599
- One, two, three. Up.
REBECCA: Keep breathing.

02:26.271 --> 02:27.306
[THUNDER CRASHING]

02:27.481 --> 02:29.346
[GRINDING NEARBY]

02:30.275 --> 02:32.391
What's happening?

02:32.569 --> 02:34.935
- The walls are getting closer.
- The dome's a sphere.

02:35.113 --> 02:37.104
It's contracting horizontally
and vertically.

02:37.282 --> 02:39.864
I think it's shutting down.
Everything inside is going haywire.

02:40.035 --> 02:42.151
We gotta get some gear
so we can explore this crater.

02:42.329 --> 02:46.117
TOM:
Help! We need help!

02:46.917 --> 02:48.373
It's near the Tilden farm.

02:48.543 --> 02:49.953
I thought we got everybody in town.

02:50.128 --> 02:51.664
Tom must have gone back
for something.

02:51.838 --> 02:53.214
Hey, keep an eye on Hunter.

02:53.382 --> 02:56.590
- Don't do anything stupid.
- Wait. Where are you going?

02:56.760 --> 02:58.591
JOE: We need to get a tablet.
HUNTER: What for?

02:58.762 --> 03:00.969
When this thing opened,
it might have created a crack.

03:01.139 --> 03:02.800
Which means we might
get a Wi-Fi signal.

03:02.974 --> 03:04.930
Maybe we can get a message
to the Hounds of Diana.

03:05.102 --> 03:06.717
If the Hounds tell us
Melanie's in Zenith,

03:06.895 --> 03:09.307
that means the crater's our way out.

03:13.485 --> 03:16.067
- Help! Help!
TOM: Aah!

03:16.238 --> 03:18.103
- What happened?
- The shaking-- It fell.

03:18.281 --> 03:19.737
- It's crushing my leg.
- Help my dad.

03:19.908 --> 03:21.489
- Please.
- Get my son out of here.

03:21.660 --> 03:23.070
[TOM YELLING]

03:23.245 --> 03:25.110
- No, I need to help.
- Go with Julia, son.

03:25.288 --> 03:27.415
- You're coming with us.
- Tom, I'll look after him.

03:27.582 --> 03:28.992
TOM:
Get him out of here.

03:29.167 --> 03:30.828
[GRUNTING AND YELLING]

03:31.002 --> 03:33.414
BARBIE: Let's try this.
TOM: I love you, buddy. Go with Julia.

03:33.588 --> 03:35.544
- Not leaving without you.
JULIA: He's gonna help.

03:35.716 --> 03:37.377
BARBIE: Try again. Here we go.
- Aah!

03:38.385 --> 03:40.171
Go! Get out! Go! Get out!

03:41.304 --> 03:44.137
- Daddy. No. Dad.
BARBIE: No. No.

03:44.307 --> 03:46.468
AIDAN: No. No.
- I think Joe's right.

03:46.643 --> 03:48.179
- The dome's shutting down.
- Dad, no!

03:48.353 --> 03:51.311
- I'm guessing we got a few hours.
- No! Dad! No!

03:51.481 --> 03:53.813
- Come on, bud. I know, buddy.
- Please, no. Dad. Dad.

03:53.984 --> 03:56.145
Come on, guys. Let's go.
We got an injured person here.

03:56.319 --> 03:58.526
SAM: Let's get her up.
Get as much gauze as you can find.

03:58.697 --> 04:00.153
JIM:
Get a table. Move it over here.

04:00.699 --> 04:02.906
Her abdomen's rigid.
She's bleeding internally.

04:03.076 --> 04:05.738
Lyle might have Iacerated an organ.
Kidney, maybe, or her liver.

04:05.912 --> 04:07.368
I know you can help. Do something.

04:07.539 --> 04:10.030
- She needs surgery.
- Operate. Do whatever you have to.

04:10.208 --> 04:12.790
I'm not a surgeon. And we don't
have anesthesia or equipment.

04:12.961 --> 04:15.168
I can't even tell which organ
is injured without an MRI.

04:15.338 --> 04:16.794
Listen, there is an answer. Find it!

04:16.965 --> 04:19.422
- Please, you have to help her.
- I'm doing everything I can.

04:22.888 --> 04:24.549
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

04:40.363 --> 04:42.274
No signal. I'm sorry.

04:42.449 --> 04:43.905
It was a good idea though.

04:44.075 --> 04:45.906
So the crater didn't create
a crack in the dome

04:46.077 --> 04:47.283
and there's no new tunnel.

04:47.454 --> 04:49.410
Maybe it did, but someone
is blocking the signal.

04:49.581 --> 04:52.539
Yeah, or it's nothing
but a giant killer suck hole.

04:53.877 --> 04:56.209
We're literally hours away
from being crushed to death.

04:56.379 --> 04:59.086
Maybe I should go find my mom
and spend my last few hours with her,

04:59.257 --> 05:02.124
instead of trying to convince myself
that whoever or whatever

05:02.302 --> 05:04.918
controls this dumb dome

05:05.096 --> 05:06.802
even gives a crap about any of us.

05:06.973 --> 05:11.216
Norrie, I need you here
with me, okay?

05:14.439 --> 05:18.023
- Hey. Hey, what are you doing?
- Plan B.

05:19.945 --> 05:21.355
Joe, you're not going down there.

05:21.530 --> 05:25.398
This is my town. Yours too now.
If we don't do anything, we all die.

05:26.618 --> 05:29.234
If we explore the crater,
we might be able to save everyone.

05:29.412 --> 05:33.701
He's right. We know the dome
better than anyone.

05:38.296 --> 05:39.911
You okay, Pauline?

05:40.423 --> 05:41.879
What happened?

05:42.050 --> 05:44.086
Lyle tried to take you away from me.

05:44.761 --> 05:46.467
He stabbed you.

05:46.638 --> 05:48.253
He's dead now.

05:48.431 --> 05:49.591
No.

05:49.766 --> 05:52.178
Everything's gonna be okay,
I promise.

05:52.352 --> 05:53.762
Mm-hm.

05:56.648 --> 05:58.479
Can we give her something
for the pain?

05:59.734 --> 06:01.110
We have morphine.

06:02.237 --> 06:03.818
Just 10 milligrams, okay?

06:08.577 --> 06:10.363
- Jim?
- Yeah?

06:10.537 --> 06:12.869
- We should talk.
- Okay. I'll be right back.

06:20.463 --> 06:22.203
She looks good. Oh the mend.

06:22.382 --> 06:23.918
The internal damage is too massive

06:24.092 --> 06:26.879
- to control without surgery.
- So do something else.

06:27.053 --> 06:29.044
I can keep her
as comfortable as possible.

06:29.222 --> 06:31.838
But there's nothing I can do
to stop her from bleeding out.

06:32.017 --> 06:33.848
What are you saying?
That she's gonna die?

06:34.019 --> 06:37.182
If there was something else,
anything, I would do it.

06:38.148 --> 06:40.184
JIM:
I don't accept that.

06:40.358 --> 06:42.610
Pauline came back to save us,

06:42.777 --> 06:44.517
not bleed out in front of her son.

06:47.324 --> 06:49.360
The dome won't let her die.

06:50.452 --> 06:51.783
This is just another test.

06:53.413 --> 06:55.904
My family, my wife,

06:56.583 --> 06:58.073
we were chosen.

06:59.711 --> 07:01.292
We gotta get Mom
back to the crater.

07:01.713 --> 07:03.920
Melanie didn'tjust disappear
into thin air.

07:04.090 --> 07:07.253
- It must lead somewhere.
SAM: I hope it does, Junior.

07:07.427 --> 07:09.543
But Pauline's injuries are too severe.

07:09.721 --> 07:12.258
If we move her,
it will accelerate the bleeding.

07:12.432 --> 07:13.592
Well, tell me what we can do.

07:13.767 --> 07:15.849
- She needs fluids.
- Where do I get saline?

07:16.019 --> 07:17.555
- Clinic?
- I'll find it.

07:18.021 --> 07:19.932
It is another tunnel.

07:20.106 --> 07:22.392
But it's different than the one
underneath the school.

07:26.446 --> 07:27.777
What are those things?

07:28.740 --> 07:31.402
I don't know. But they're cool.

07:32.160 --> 07:33.320
[RUMBUNG]

07:33.495 --> 07:35.531
Yeah, and kind of terrifying.

07:41.711 --> 07:44.123
All right, let's do this.

07:47.342 --> 07:49.628
JOE: Maybe we can figure out
what happened to Melanie.

07:53.348 --> 07:55.054
Be careful.

08:00.188 --> 08:01.769
Come on.

08:07.612 --> 08:11.605
- You okay, Mom?
- Just a little pain.

08:11.783 --> 08:13.648
Can we give her
some more morphine?

08:14.244 --> 08:16.485
We don't wanna
give her an overdose.

08:16.663 --> 08:18.824
No, Junior. It's okay.

08:20.375 --> 08:22.240
- Dad's coming back.
- Mm.

08:22.419 --> 08:25.536
Okay? We're gonna fix you up.
Just like Melanie.

08:25.714 --> 08:28.251
Do you think she's okay?
That she made it out?

08:29.050 --> 08:30.665
Anything's possible.

08:31.886 --> 08:35.970
Mm. My brushes. And canvas.

08:36.141 --> 08:39.679
- What do you mean?
- Maybe I can paint the way out.

08:42.605 --> 08:44.106
Junior, it's important.

08:45.525 --> 08:46.856
Go get them.

08:47.819 --> 08:49.275
James.

08:49.779 --> 08:52.361
We've been through so much.

08:55.243 --> 08:58.155
I got to see my sweet,

08:58.329 --> 09:00.194
sweet boy become a man.

09:09.507 --> 09:11.293
I love you, Mom.

09:11.468 --> 09:13.299
I love you.

09:13.845 --> 09:15.085
Forever.

09:26.775 --> 09:29.812
What you said to Junior,
it sounded like a goodbye.

09:29.986 --> 09:31.851
We both know the truth.

09:32.030 --> 09:33.691
I'm not going to make it.

09:33.865 --> 09:35.480
We just have to get you stable.

09:36.451 --> 09:38.612
If the crater's the way out,
we'll take you.

09:38.787 --> 09:40.152
No.

09:40.330 --> 09:42.195
The dome's done with me.

09:42.373 --> 09:44.079
I saw my own death.

09:44.584 --> 09:48.327
- Pauline.
- All that matters is Junior.

09:48.505 --> 09:50.666
That he survives.

09:52.133 --> 09:55.296
And Jim won't let me go.

09:55.470 --> 09:57.085
I don't want that.

09:57.263 --> 10:00.630
- What are you saying?
- Let me go peacefully.

10:01.810 --> 10:04.847
Becky. Help me.

10:05.021 --> 10:06.602
Please.

10:10.235 --> 10:12.100
I think you were supposed
to be here for this.

10:12.278 --> 10:14.485
I don't know about that.

10:15.156 --> 10:17.112
I gotta go grab that gear,
get back to the crater.

10:17.283 --> 10:20.070
- Figure out what's down there.
- We should split up.

10:20.245 --> 10:22.907
I'll take Aidan back to the high school
while you head back.

10:23.957 --> 10:25.743
Well, wait for me
at the school, all right?

10:25.917 --> 10:28.579
Grab a walkie from Sam.
I'll be in touch.

10:28.753 --> 10:30.289
[RUMBLING THEN
GRINDING NEARBY]

10:30.463 --> 10:33.626
All right, honey.
We're gonna head this way, okay?

10:34.425 --> 10:36.131
[RUMBUNG]

10:36.302 --> 10:38.714
HUNTER:
What do we do about this fork?

10:40.431 --> 10:42.558
- Which way?
- I have no idea.

10:42.725 --> 10:44.386
[NORRIE GASPS]

10:44.561 --> 10:46.347
Joe, look.

10:50.984 --> 10:52.690
[RUMBLING INTENSIFIES]

10:56.447 --> 10:57.903
I think we just made our decision.

10:59.033 --> 11:01.365
HUNTER: How long do you think
the crater's gonna stay open?

11:01.536 --> 11:03.527
I don't know. Not long.

11:03.705 --> 11:06.196
We gotta tell Barbie.
There might be a way out.

11:18.136 --> 11:20.593
Come on. Norrie. Come on, jump.

11:20.763 --> 11:23.175
Come on, let's go.

11:28.062 --> 11:31.395
Hey. What the hell
do you think you're doing?

11:31.566 --> 11:32.897
- We went down.
- Yeah, I see that.

11:33.067 --> 11:35.524
What part of "don't do anything stupid"
did you not understand?

11:35.695 --> 11:38.937
Don't be pissed. We couldn't wait.
We found more tunnels.

11:39.115 --> 11:40.616
There was a monarch
down there too.

11:40.783 --> 11:42.944
It showed us a path
with a light at the end.

11:43.119 --> 11:44.484
Did you see where it goes?

11:44.662 --> 11:46.493
We had to get out.
Things are shaky down there.

11:46.664 --> 11:48.165
The passage may not
be open for long.

11:48.333 --> 11:50.164
But it goes somewhere.
And, like I said before,

11:50.335 --> 11:51.666
anywhere is better than here.

11:51.836 --> 11:54.293
And it doesn't look like your dad's
showing up with the egg.

11:55.006 --> 11:57.167
The time between these contractions
is getting shorter.

11:57.342 --> 11:59.207
[THUNDER CRASHES]

11:59.385 --> 12:01.717
JOE: And the dome's
making the weather worse.

12:01.888 --> 12:04.721
All right, well, we're going
down the crater. It's our only shot.

12:05.141 --> 12:06.176
[RADIO BEEPS]

12:06.351 --> 12:08.057
Julia.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.684
I think we got another chance.

12:09.854 --> 12:12.687
- This might be the way out of here.
- Thanks.

12:12.857 --> 12:15.690
Sam. Rebecca.

12:15.860 --> 12:18.351
The crater could be the way out.
We gotta gather the town.

12:18.529 --> 12:20.360
Okay, well,
most everyone's either here

12:20.531 --> 12:22.032
or at the Sweetbriar or the church.

12:22.200 --> 12:24.361
Round them up.
We gotta get everybody to the woods.

12:24.535 --> 12:26.275
- How?
JULIA: All right.

12:27.705 --> 12:30.321
School busses. They run on diesel,
there's a whole fleet.

12:30.500 --> 12:31.956
Gotta be fuel left in some of them.

12:32.126 --> 12:34.082
I'll check. Gather the wounded,
get them on first.

12:34.254 --> 12:37.371
All right, anyone who can't fit
on the buses will just walk.

12:40.551 --> 12:42.132
Jim, what are you doing here?

12:42.303 --> 12:44.214
I'm looking for saline.
Someone's hurt.

12:44.389 --> 12:46.755
Didn't you hear the plan?
We're leaving. Everyone.

12:46.933 --> 12:50.346
- Did you find any saline?
- No. Leave it.

12:50.520 --> 12:53.512
We have to round everyone up.
Julia said there isn't much time.

12:53.690 --> 12:56.773
Listen, if I don't find that saline,
my wife dies.

12:58.528 --> 12:59.984
I knew it. It was waiting for me.

13:03.574 --> 13:06.065
Hey. Your mom's here.

13:06.244 --> 13:09.077
Julia wants our help
loading up the busses.

13:10.540 --> 13:12.280
What's wrong?

13:16.004 --> 13:17.995
Do you really think
we're gonna get out?

13:18.172 --> 13:20.584
I mean, the tunnels are freaky,
but, yeah, we'll make it.

13:22.051 --> 13:24.793
It's not the tunnels.

13:25.722 --> 13:27.178
It's what's after that.

13:28.224 --> 13:31.466
Am I just supposed to go back
to my life in California?

13:31.644 --> 13:33.976
Without my mom?

13:37.734 --> 13:39.975
How can I go
and just leave her here?

13:40.153 --> 13:42.439
She's not here.

13:42.905 --> 13:44.770
Neither is Angie.

13:44.949 --> 13:46.485
They might be buried
in Chester's Mill,

13:46.659 --> 13:49.116
but they'll always be with us.

13:50.872 --> 13:53.238
Do you know why
I was going to boot camp?

13:53.750 --> 13:56.583
Why I'm here in the first place?

13:56.753 --> 13:58.914
I assumed you got
into some kind of trouble.

14:02.216 --> 14:04.798
I punched some stupid girl
in the mouth

14:04.969 --> 14:07.301
and knocked her tooth out.

14:08.264 --> 14:11.597
And all she did
was make fun of my hair.

14:13.144 --> 14:18.935
It's just so stupid
to think how much I cared.

14:19.233 --> 14:22.475
- Ifl had just ignored her--
- No, the dome wanted you here.

14:22.653 --> 14:24.029
It would've found another way.

14:24.197 --> 14:26.984
I don't care what the dome wanted.

14:28.993 --> 14:30.984
Because I just want my mom.

14:34.165 --> 14:35.871
Sometimes I think on Dome Day,

14:36.042 --> 14:39.079
if Angie and Ijust went
to brunch with my mom...

14:40.922 --> 14:42.583
But then I never would've met you.

14:46.135 --> 14:49.719
My mom told me before she died
to be brave.

14:53.059 --> 14:55.801
And Ijust don't feel brave right now.

14:59.899 --> 15:03.687
Look, I don't know
what's gonna happen.

15:05.196 --> 15:07.528
But whatever's out there,

15:08.032 --> 15:10.273
we're gonna face it together.

15:11.536 --> 15:13.527
Okay.

15:17.500 --> 15:19.240
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

15:38.479 --> 15:41.437
No. No.

15:49.574 --> 15:52.566
REBECCA: Pauline? There's news.
The passage you opened?

15:52.743 --> 15:54.825
We're evacuating everyone
through it.

15:54.996 --> 15:57.362
So if you can just hold on,

15:57.540 --> 15:59.371
we can try to get you to a doctor.

15:59.542 --> 16:03.251
Oh. I won't make it.

16:03.921 --> 16:06.253
I'll only slow down the people I love.

16:06.424 --> 16:08.881
It's just a little longer. You can do it.

16:09.427 --> 16:11.543
No, this is what the dome wants.

16:11.721 --> 16:14.383
I paid for my sins.

16:14.557 --> 16:15.717
[SIGHS]

16:15.892 --> 16:21.057
For once, I'll be able to sleep
without dreaming.

16:21.230 --> 16:23.767
No, there's hope now.

16:24.442 --> 16:26.433
We're only getting out
because of you.

16:26.611 --> 16:31.355
Good. Junior will be safe.

16:31.532 --> 16:32.567
[GROANS]

16:32.742 --> 16:36.155
This is so much pain.

16:36.996 --> 16:40.909
Please be kind. Please.

16:48.257 --> 16:50.669
Oh, sweet girl.

16:51.010 --> 16:53.296
What a sweet girl.

17:09.237 --> 17:11.319
Can you help me
and make sure everyone has a seat?

17:11.489 --> 17:13.980
- Yeah, okay.
- Thanks, Aidan.

17:14.158 --> 17:16.570
Rain. Because it wasn't enough
of a mess already?

17:16.744 --> 17:18.609
The dome's contractions
must be messing

17:18.788 --> 17:20.449
with the weather patterns
or something.

17:20.623 --> 17:22.159
NORRIE: No.
CAROLYN: Come with me now.

17:22.333 --> 17:24.619
I told you a hundred times,
I need to stay here.

17:24.794 --> 17:28.252
- I'm one of the four hands. I'm sorry.
- I'm not asking you, Eleanor.

17:28.422 --> 17:30.413
Hey, hey, hey.
Norrie, do me a favor, okay?

17:30.591 --> 17:32.707
Get on this first bus.
I'm really gonna need your help

17:32.885 --> 17:35.171
- once we get to that crater.
- Okay.

17:35.346 --> 17:37.758
Thank you. Okay, come on.

17:38.975 --> 17:41.466
Julia. Have you seen Andrea?

17:41.644 --> 17:43.885
She's getting supplies.
She's gonna meet us at the crater.

17:44.063 --> 17:45.599
[THUNDER CRASHES]

17:57.535 --> 18:00.527
All right, don't stop.
Let's go. Keep moving. Load up.

18:00.705 --> 18:02.195
Keep moving.

18:02.373 --> 18:04.034
Hey, where's Pauline?

18:04.208 --> 18:06.324
She's still inside.
We're waiting for Jim to get back.

18:06.502 --> 18:08.333
Well, he better hurry with that saline.

18:08.504 --> 18:10.870
- How is your sister?
JIM: Let me through.

18:11.048 --> 18:12.458
Hey, I got the saline.

18:12.633 --> 18:14.464
- I got the saline. Come on.
- We gotta hurry.

18:14.635 --> 18:16.546
Do what you can for Pauline
and then let's go.

18:16.721 --> 18:18.461
I'll see you soon.

18:18.639 --> 18:20.220
Baby. I got it for you.

18:20.391 --> 18:22.723
I found the stuff you need.

18:22.893 --> 18:24.929
I told you the dome
was looking after us.

18:25.896 --> 18:28.228
Pauline. I'm back, honey.

18:28.399 --> 18:31.391
Sam, my pain is gone.

18:31.569 --> 18:34.857
Oh, that's good, that's good.
That's real good.

18:37.074 --> 18:38.689
I told you it's gonna be okay.

18:39.744 --> 18:42.110
I know you love me.

18:42.288 --> 18:45.451
- I'm sorry.
- You don't need to be sorry.

18:48.919 --> 18:51.251
You don't need to be sorry.

18:53.466 --> 18:56.503
Pauline? Look at me.

19:05.102 --> 19:08.014
- What's wrong?
- Her pulse is dropping.

19:09.065 --> 19:11.226
Oh, and take care of Junior.

19:12.818 --> 19:16.857
- Pauline.
- I love you all.

19:27.249 --> 19:29.831
I just got you back.

19:52.692 --> 19:53.772
You did this.

19:55.695 --> 19:58.357
She said it was
what the dome wanted.

19:58.948 --> 20:00.779
She begged me.

20:00.950 --> 20:03.157
You always have the solutions,
don't you?

20:05.204 --> 20:07.616
It was a kind thing to do. I'm sorry.

20:07.790 --> 20:11.499
Always got something in your
back pocket for every emergency.

20:13.129 --> 20:14.539
It was her last request.

20:14.714 --> 20:16.830
Oh, now you can kill?

20:17.758 --> 20:18.998
When it's my wife?

20:19.176 --> 20:23.840
Jim, if Pauline thought
that this is what the dome wanted--

20:24.014 --> 20:26.175
The dome wanted
my family together.

20:28.811 --> 20:30.142
And you got in the way.

20:30.312 --> 20:32.303
Walk away, Jim.

20:32.481 --> 20:34.938
Go find Junior
and get him out of here.

20:57.673 --> 20:59.288
I'll miss my wife forever.

21:01.177 --> 21:02.838
No one's gonna miss you.

21:15.399 --> 21:17.060
Mom?

21:17.902 --> 21:20.689
Mom.Mom.

21:23.449 --> 21:24.734
Oh, my God.

21:26.702 --> 21:28.238
[SAM GROANING]

21:29.288 --> 21:32.325
Sam. You okay?

21:32.500 --> 21:33.740
Get up.

21:33.918 --> 21:34.953
What happened?

21:38.297 --> 21:39.582
SAM:
Oh, my God. No.

21:40.257 --> 21:41.292
Where's Mom?

21:42.259 --> 21:44.045
She's gone.

21:44.220 --> 21:46.586
- What do you mean?
- Pauline asked Rebecca

21:46.764 --> 21:50.473
to help her end her life.

21:50.643 --> 21:52.304
She was in so much pain.

21:55.481 --> 21:57.642
Jim went after Rebecca.

21:57.817 --> 22:00.559
I tried to stop him. I couldn't.

22:02.446 --> 22:04.357
I'm so sorry, Junior.

22:24.426 --> 22:27.213
Mom was trying to say goodbye.

22:28.430 --> 22:30.216
- I should've known.
- We gotta find your dad.

22:30.391 --> 22:32.222
He's gone crazy.
We gotta talk him down.

22:32.393 --> 22:33.758
Why would I do that?

22:33.936 --> 22:36.848
There's no talking to him.
There's only dealing with him.

22:39.483 --> 22:42.099
Why'd you paint that, Pauline?

22:44.822 --> 22:46.938
I wish you hadn't.

23:17.771 --> 23:19.056
Dome?

23:19.523 --> 23:21.309
I'll make you a deal.

23:24.111 --> 23:26.773
If you bring her back right now,

23:31.493 --> 23:37.830
I won't murder every single one
of your special little friends.

23:40.252 --> 23:43.460
I won't slit Julia's throat,

23:45.674 --> 23:48.051
shoot Barbie in the heart

23:49.637 --> 23:52.674
or burn those kids alive.

23:55.392 --> 23:57.007
Okay?

24:01.523 --> 24:04.060
You got three seconds.

24:25.923 --> 24:27.754
Okay, then.

24:38.519 --> 24:41.261
I'm gonna free you from all this,

24:43.482 --> 24:47.066
so you can go right
through the dome wall.

24:49.238 --> 24:52.446
And it's gonna regret
what it did to us.

25:02.334 --> 25:03.574
I promise.

25:42.041 --> 25:44.248
This is the same plan
that we had before.

25:44.418 --> 25:46.579
We're all gonna break up
into small groups

25:46.754 --> 25:47.994
keeping your family with you.

25:48.172 --> 25:51.005
We will call you forward
one by one and get you down.

25:51.175 --> 25:53.086
Once your entire group is down,

25:53.260 --> 25:55.000
Joe and Norrie here
will guide you into the--

25:55.179 --> 25:56.464
How do you know this is safe?

25:56.638 --> 25:59.300
[MURMURING]

26:00.726 --> 26:02.216
I know because I've done it before.

26:05.689 --> 26:08.180
And look, I know you're all scared.

26:09.026 --> 26:11.233
Okay? I know that I'm a stranger.

26:11.403 --> 26:12.563
But for the last two weeks,

26:12.738 --> 26:15.696
we have fought together
for the survival of this town.

26:15.866 --> 26:18.073
But right now,
I need you to trust me,

26:18.243 --> 26:19.858
because we don't have
another choice.

26:20.037 --> 26:22.323
If we stay here, we die.

26:26.376 --> 26:29.334
Now, come on. Let's get out of here.

26:30.380 --> 26:32.041
GIRL: Mommy, I'm scared.
- Carolyn, listen,

26:32.216 --> 26:35.708
I need you to go down with me. Okay?
Help me keep everyone calm.

26:35.886 --> 26:39.720
Julia, Hunter, hey. Can I get you guys
to stay at the top here? All right?

26:39.890 --> 26:41.255
Keep everything orderly.

26:41.433 --> 26:43.640
Make sure we don't
leave anyone behind.

26:43.811 --> 26:44.846
Am I forgetting anything?

26:45.562 --> 26:48.304
No. You're doing exactly
what you're supposed to.

26:48.482 --> 26:50.063
I love you.

26:50.609 --> 26:52.474
I love you too.

26:54.321 --> 26:56.687
All right, you guys ready? Let's do it.

27:02.371 --> 27:04.612
All right, everybody, group one.
Stick with me.

27:04.790 --> 27:07.327
Just stay calm, all right?
We're gonna be fine.

27:07.751 --> 27:09.412
- Let's go.
MAN: You heard him.

27:10.003 --> 27:11.539
Keep moving.

27:13.423 --> 27:15.163
[RUMBUNG]

27:16.593 --> 27:18.208
Hold on. Hold on.

27:22.474 --> 27:24.135
It's okay, guys.
We've been here before.

27:24.309 --> 27:25.640
There's no need to be afraid.

27:27.271 --> 27:29.102
Careful.

27:30.190 --> 27:31.225
All right, Carolyn.

27:35.320 --> 27:37.697
[PEOPLE SHOUTING
INDISTINCTLY]

27:37.865 --> 27:39.901
WOMAN: Stop.
- The cracks are getting wider.

27:46.165 --> 27:47.530
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

27:50.294 --> 27:52.501
CAROLYN:
You're fine, you're fine.

27:52.671 --> 27:55.629
All right, everybody,
watch your step, all right?

27:55.799 --> 27:56.914
We'll help you across.

27:58.677 --> 27:59.837
HUNTER:
Okay, how we doing?

28:00.012 --> 28:01.422
Most folks are accounted for.

28:01.597 --> 28:03.963
ANDREA [OVER RADIO]:
Julia. Please be there.

28:04.725 --> 28:05.885
Andrea?

28:06.059 --> 28:08.220
- What's wrong? Where are you?
ANDREA: I'm at my house.

28:08.395 --> 28:10.386
[WHIMPERING]
[need help. /-- Oh, God.

28:10.564 --> 28:12.646
Andrea? Andrea.

28:16.069 --> 28:17.275
Andrea.

28:39.301 --> 28:40.586
Andrea?

28:52.689 --> 28:54.645
Andrea?

28:54.816 --> 28:56.772
ANDREA:
In here.

29:03.659 --> 29:04.944
I knew you'd come running.

29:06.703 --> 29:08.785
Put the bat down.

29:13.252 --> 29:15.368
SAM [OVER RADIO]:
Julia? Come in.

29:18.382 --> 29:20.043
- Less is more.
SAM: Julia.

29:30.227 --> 29:31.512
Hey, Sam. What do you need?

29:31.687 --> 29:32.847
SAM:
You okay?

29:39.111 --> 29:41.648
Yeah, I'm just helping Andrea.
We're headed back now.

29:41.822 --> 29:44.939
Junior and I are at the crater
with Hunter.

29:45.367 --> 29:48.450
Listen, you should know, uh,
Pauline is dead.

29:49.913 --> 29:51.778
And Jim killed Rebecca.

29:51.957 --> 29:53.913
He ’3 out there somewhere.

29:56.295 --> 29:57.410
Gotta go now, Sam.

30:05.304 --> 30:06.419
What are you doing, Jim?

30:07.597 --> 30:08.757
Payback.

30:08.932 --> 30:10.388
ANDREA:
Against me?

30:10.559 --> 30:14.222
What did I ever do
except be your neighbor and friend?

30:15.397 --> 30:16.682
It's not about you, honey.

30:17.524 --> 30:19.355
[DISHES BREAKING]

30:23.864 --> 30:27.903
Sam forgot to mention
that Rebecca murdered Pauline.

30:29.286 --> 30:33.495
Yeah. I gave the dome a chance
to return her to me.

30:33.665 --> 30:35.997
But it declined.

30:37.210 --> 30:39.462
Which is bad for you.

30:39.629 --> 30:42.086
Killing me won't bring Pauline back.

30:42.257 --> 30:46.626
Yeah, but it might ruin
some of the dome's plans,

30:46.803 --> 30:48.964
and that's good enough.

30:52.559 --> 30:53.924
JULIA:
Andrea was your friend.

30:54.686 --> 30:56.847
Yeah, I know.

30:57.022 --> 30:58.853
That's why I killed her quick.

31:01.443 --> 31:02.899
You don't get that privilege.

31:06.323 --> 31:07.813
[PANTING]

31:19.920 --> 31:21.581
[JULIA GRUNTS]

31:26.510 --> 31:29.718
You know why the dome
didn't bring Pauline back?

31:29.888 --> 31:31.219
Because you're a joke.

31:31.390 --> 31:35.759
Because the dome doesn't make deals
with insects like you.

31:36.186 --> 31:38.222
Even your wife knew
you were meaningless.

31:38.397 --> 31:40.604
I'll like you a lot better
when your mouth's broken.

31:41.691 --> 31:43.192
[YELLS]

31:43.944 --> 31:45.434
[GRUNTING]

31:53.787 --> 31:55.869
All right, everybody. Come on.
Keep moving forward.

31:56.039 --> 31:59.122
Keep moving forward, you'll catch up
with the next group, all right? Let's go.

31:59.292 --> 32:02.284
Everything's gonna be fine.
All right, Julia, how many we got left?

32:04.047 --> 32:06.333
Uh, only a few.
I'm sending them down now.

32:06.508 --> 32:08.794
- Where's Julia?
- She left to help a friend.

32:08.969 --> 32:10.300
Where is she right now?

32:10.470 --> 32:12.677
I don't know.
She's not answering her walkie.

32:18.562 --> 32:20.723
[GUNSHOTS THEN
JULIA SHRIEKS]

32:21.398 --> 32:22.729
JUNIOR:
Julia.

32:23.400 --> 32:25.231
Here!

32:27.070 --> 32:28.355
You okay?

32:28.530 --> 32:30.612
Jim killed Andrea. He's behind me.

32:31.658 --> 32:33.569
- Junior.
- Go without me.

32:33.743 --> 32:36.155
- No. I'm not gonna let you go alone.
- I said go.

32:38.415 --> 32:40.326
Put your arm around me.

32:47.382 --> 32:48.417
What are you doing, son?

32:48.884 --> 32:50.090
I'm not your son anymore.

32:51.428 --> 32:52.918
I'm not gonna let you
hurt anyone else.

32:53.096 --> 32:54.131
How you gonna do that?

32:57.142 --> 32:59.053
You're not leaving this town.

33:00.729 --> 33:01.935
You don't tell me what to do.

33:03.023 --> 33:05.730
Not you, not the dome.

33:06.735 --> 33:08.225
This is my town, little boy.

33:16.286 --> 33:18.402
Enjoy what's left of it.

33:25.003 --> 33:26.539
[JULIA GRUNTS]

33:33.595 --> 33:36.257
Oh, God. You made it.

33:39.017 --> 33:40.052
What happened?

33:40.227 --> 33:42.138
- Jim.
- Where is he?

33:42.312 --> 33:45.679
Barbie, there's no time.
Junior's taking care of it.

33:45.857 --> 33:47.017
Jim's not getting down here.

33:48.276 --> 33:51.484
All right, I'll take her. Let's go.

33:51.655 --> 33:53.395
Can you take Aidan up ahead?

33:53.573 --> 33:55.655
You just go on, all right?
I'll be right behind you.

33:55.825 --> 33:57.406
- Okay.
SAM: Come on.

33:57.577 --> 33:59.317
Hunter, go up front
with Joe and Norrie.

33:59.496 --> 34:01.908
- Tell them to move out, all right?
- Okay.

34:02.582 --> 34:04.163
We'll catch up.

34:04.334 --> 34:06.199
Nice and slow.

34:07.546 --> 34:09.958
[RUMBUNG]

34:11.258 --> 34:12.873
JIM:
Junior!

34:14.010 --> 34:16.092
[JULIA PANTING]

34:17.055 --> 34:18.386
You all right?

34:20.225 --> 34:22.216
You're gonna have to jump.
You think you can do it?

34:22.394 --> 34:23.850
- Yeah, I can make it.
- Okay.

34:24.020 --> 34:26.056
I'll get across
and I'll give you a hand.

34:31.027 --> 34:32.983
All right, come on.
Step up, give me your hand.

34:33.154 --> 34:34.234
Okay.

34:35.740 --> 34:37.150
[RUMBUNG]

34:54.467 --> 34:55.502
I can't make it.

34:56.761 --> 34:59.093
No. There's gotta be another way.
I'm not leaving you here.

34:59.264 --> 35:00.629
You don't have a choice.

35:00.807 --> 35:03.594
The town needs your help. And fast,
before the tunnels cave in on them.

35:03.768 --> 35:06.145
- The dome chose you.
- Barbie, listen to me.

35:07.856 --> 35:11.974
Pauline had a vision of someone
guiding everyone out of the dome.

35:12.319 --> 35:14.355
She didn't see his face, but it's you.

35:18.575 --> 35:21.066
But everything we've done
for this town we've done together.

35:21.244 --> 35:24.236
It's okay,
the dome has gotten us this far.

35:24.664 --> 35:28.657
I have faith
that if you do what it's asking,

35:30.045 --> 35:31.080
it will protect me.

35:31.796 --> 35:34.082
[RUMBLING CONTINUES]

35:43.725 --> 35:45.181
I'm coming back for you.

35:45.935 --> 35:47.800
I know.

36:12.003 --> 36:13.584
Junior!

36:15.048 --> 36:17.414
Junior, you can't leave me!

36:31.815 --> 36:33.726
Junior!

36:34.984 --> 36:37.236
Barbie, where's Julia?

36:37.404 --> 36:40.020
She's coming.
She sent me up ahead.

36:43.243 --> 36:46.235
- Why is everybody stopped?
- Nobody knows which way to go.

36:46.413 --> 36:49.405
Barbie, we need to go this way.
We saw the butterfly go down there.

36:49.582 --> 36:52.494
I think it's a sign. Both Joe and I do.

36:55.338 --> 36:57.750
All right, this is the way, okay?

36:57.924 --> 37:00.006
Everybody follow me.

37:00.176 --> 37:02.167
[CHATTERING]

37:09.477 --> 37:10.512
What happened?

37:13.231 --> 37:15.222
Barbie went ahead.
He'll come back for us.

37:17.026 --> 37:19.278
Then we'll figure out a way across.

38:07.827 --> 38:09.408
No, this can't be all that's there.

38:09.579 --> 38:11.115
- It can't be.
- Is this a cave-in?

38:11.289 --> 38:12.574
Barbie, what do we do now?

38:14.542 --> 38:15.577
I don't-- I don't know.

38:15.752 --> 38:18.994
No, we didn't come all this way
for a dead end.

38:20.006 --> 38:21.041
Screw you!

38:22.258 --> 38:23.714
Can you hear me?

38:23.885 --> 38:25.921
Whoever you are
controlling all of this,

38:26.095 --> 38:29.223
can you just talk to us
and tell us what's going on?

38:29.390 --> 38:31.096
[NORRIE PANTING]

39:09.347 --> 39:10.427
How did you...?

39:10.598 --> 39:11.974
[ROCKS CRACKING]

39:12.141 --> 39:14.473
I have no idea.

39:18.439 --> 39:19.599
What's that noise?

39:33.496 --> 39:34.906
Melanie?

39:35.540 --> 39:37.405
Follow me.

39:37.584 --> 39:38.949
We're going home.
